title: Collective Health takes $81M from Google Ventures, others, to go nationwide
text: Collective Health says today it’s taking a large new funding round from Google Ventures and others to offer its health insurance management platform to employers nationwide in 2016. The $81 million funding round comes from first-time investor Google Ventures and existing investors NEA and Founders Fund, along with Maverick Capital, Redpoint Ventures and RRE Ventures.
